I'm farming the focus Stein and Shovel on my Main currently which should be nice presents for Meato's Christmas.  Any other focus effect items i should pick up?  Giving up a toon I worked on for a year to put all my effort into a Mage is a huge descision for me.  Thanks in advance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hexxis00>Hexxis00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/02 12:01:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1103.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/dc/dbvortex/Vortexgifanimations/PiccoloBeamCannon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Switching Mains</span><hr size=1> Mages can level fast when played by the right person.<br>
However it seems to me that no amount of gear can make a mage level any faster than he would ordinarily. Best Idea for you would be to do is get as much FT and mana/HP items as you can,(along with int) and spend the rest of the cash on donations for KEI since THAT is the spell that will make a huge difference on leveling time for certain,.. and learn the most effecients ways for you to kill mobs... hordes of blues always worked for me cause it's takes less mana to do it and also saves your pet and with KEI at, least with my wizard when he was leveling up, I was able to get 1 level for every KEI I had so that makes a difference. <p>Hexxis Letalis<br>
