<br>
Apart from that, INT casters are much much less about gear than melee characters. Mages are about skills. Mages are played differently, you need to learn Mage skills: <br>
<br>
- How to keep the balance between overnuking and keeping the pet alive.<br>
- How to single pull without any of the typical pull spells.<br>
- How to manage your aggro in every situation, when to stay low on aggro, when to overnuke on purpose.<br>
- How to apply Mage Kiting.<br>
- How to work with distance.<br>
- etc.: Read the boards here to get an idea.<br>
<br>
All these skills can be applied naked with just a few malachite and make the difference between a great mage and a mediocre mage. They can help make the difference between a hard wipe recovery and an easy one in a raid situation - you don't want to start learning them in the high end game when others rely on you.<br>
<br>
That said, I would go for twink items that reduce downtime. 10K isn't enough for uber items, but it is enough to get some INT/mana/HP boosts. Extended Range would be something to try, play around with casting bolts from max range. <p>Blana Foflana,<br>
